            I am writing to express my strong interest in applying for the Data & Analytics Specialist position at ROCHE. I have more than 12 years of experience in data science and risk management, I believe I possess the necessary skills and knowledge to make a significant contribution to your team.
        </p>
        <p>
            My academic background includes a Master's degree in Financial Risk Management from the Instituto Politécnico Nacional and a Bachelor's degree in Actuarial Science from the Universidad Nacional Autónoma de México. Additionally, I have completed various training programs and certifications that complement my practical experience in data analysis and predictive modeling.
        </p>
        <p>
            In my current role as a Team Lead for Data Scientists/Engineers at Allianz Insurance Spain, I have been responsible for managing and developing best practices in the P&C sector. I have led the implementation of Pricing MLOps solutions using tools such as Python, Spark, and Power BI, Git Hub, etc. Achieving substantial improvements in the accuracy and efficiency of our pricing models for automobiles, homes, and fleets.
        </p>
        <p>
            This MLOps was recognized by the Global P&C team and is now an institutional tool used at Allianz Spain.
        </p>
        <p>
            My experience at Zurich Insurance allowed me to apply advanced Machine Learning techniques to optimize the competitiveness of our pricing and significantly contribute to price optimization.
        </p>
        <p>
            My tenure at SAS Institute is also noteworthy, where I analyzed data and needs for various institutions. Among the most important projects, I highlight the creation of recurrent neural networks to predict ICU admissions for COVID-19, optimization models for the Solvay factory in Belgium, and data traffic analysis for Telefónica, as well as market and credit risk projects in the banking sector.
        </p>
        <p>
            I have extensive experience in AWS Cloud and SAS Viya environments, in addition to team management and staff training, with work experience in Mexico, Belgium, and Spain. This experience has allowed me to develop a strong ability to lead teams, coordinate complex projects, and transform business needs into effective analytical solutions.
        </p>
